ast, exacerbated by foreign intervention, led to the rise and growth of ISIS—and why addressing those problems is the only way to ensure its end. An authoritative introduction to arguably the most important conflict in the world today, this is an essential book for anyone seeking a deeper understanding of the social turmoil and political violence ravaging the Arab-Islamic world.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 25. Feb 2021) 0aIslamic fundamentalism. 0aJihad. 0aTerrorismxReligious aspectsxIslam. 0aTerrorismzMiddle East. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / World / Middle Eastern.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978140088036240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781400880362423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781400880362.jpg  aGBV-deGruyter-alles